    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-08-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="542"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Van
                        Limburg</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25,</hi> 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 22d instant, in relation to the suspension of the consular
                    functions of Mr. Conturié, and the provisional appointment of the Count Mejan,
                    the consul of France at New Orleans, to take charge of the Netherlands
                    consulate.</p>
                <p>It is inferred that you had not, at the date of your note, received my
                    communication of the 20th instant, in which, it is hoped, the subject of the
                    controversy between General Butler and Mr. Conturié has been disposed of to the
                    satisfaction of the government of the Netherlands. In accordance with your
                    request, the Count Mejan will be recognized as temporary consul of his Majesty
                    the King of the Netherlands.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of this opportunity to renew to you, sir, the assurance of my high
                    consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roest Van Limburg,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
